OL,3,C'I was exploited', says woman who
OL,4,Cworked for politician illegally
OL,6,FA Rwandan national who worked for a
OL,7,FJersey politician who was sentenced to
OL,8,Fcommunity service for immigration
OL,9,Foffences, says the judgement "does not
OL,10,Freflect the full reality or scale of
OL,11,Fthe harm" she experienced.
OL,13,FLiliane Gikundiro who was illegally
OL,14,Femployed by Deputy Philip Ozouf has
OL,15,Fspoken out after he was given 120
OL,16,Fhours community service for five
OL,17,Fimmigration offences.
