OL,3,C'I was exploited', says woman who
OL,4,Cworked for politician illegally
OL,6,FDespite having a visa to work in
OL,7,Fhospitality, Ozouf employed her to
OL,8,Fclean his house and canvas for his
OL,9,Felection in 2022. She was one of five
OL,10,Fworkers he employed to work for him,
OL,11,Feven though they only had visas to
OL,12,Fwork in hospitality.
OL,14,FOzouf had pleaded guilty to four
OL,15,Fcounts of assisting unlawful
OL,16,Fimmigration and one count of
OL,17,Fattempting to assist unlawful
OL,18,Fimmigration - the offences span from
OL,19,FDecember 2021 to May 2023.
