OL,3,C'I was exploited', says woman who
OL,4,Cworked for politician illegally
OL,6,FLiliane said she respects the court
OL,7,Fbut the outcome does not reflect the
OL,8,Ffact that she was "exploited, required
OL,9,Fto carry out unpaid labour beyond her
OL,10,Fpermit", and as a result "experienced
OL,11,Fa serious deterioration in her mental
OL,12,Fhealth."
OL,14,FShe added: "As a result, I lost my
OL,15,Fimmigration status, my livelihood, and
OL,16,Fthe life I had built. Those
OL,17,Fconsequences remain.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/7
