OL,3,C'I was exploited', says woman who
OL,4,Cworked for politician illegally
OL,6,F"Jersey Customs and Immigration said
OL,7,Fin their statement 'Ozouf deliberately
OL,8,Fand knowingly arranged for Rwandan
OL,9,Fmigrant workers to undertake work
OL,10,Fwhich fell outside the conditions of
OL,11,Ftheir work permits."
OL,13,FIt adds: "Given the gravity and nature
OL,14,Fof these offences, Reform Jersey
OL,15,Fquestions whether it is appropriate
OL,16,Ffor Deputy Ozouf to continue serving
OL,17,Fas a Member of the States.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/7
